item.description:
‼️ BREAKING ‼️ Italian AI Law approved by the Senate 📢 
The text has passed its second approval with only minor revision.

✔️ Key revisions:

-Protection of minors of 14 y.o., requiring both parents' consent to access AI;

-Transparency obligation for minors between the age of 14 and 18;

-Inclusion of democracy and fundamental rights as primary values to protect;

-Deletion of the obligation to use national data centers for data storing;

-Deletion of the obligation of Ethical Review Board approval for AI in medical research;

- The Government cannot impose further obligations with respect to the AI Act;

-A Coordination Committee for policy-making activities for institutions, organizations, and foundations operating in the field of digital innovation and artificial intelligence is established.

✅ Major benefit of this law:
- It is no longer needed the long approval procedure by the DPA for the processing of personal data in AI medical research, which prevented retrospective studies.
-Such processing is now declared of significant public interest.

For an analysis of key provisions of this law, please read my article in AIRe – Journal of AI Law and Regulation (link in the comments).

♻️ Share with doctors, researchers, and DPOs to inform them
➕ Follow me for more on AI &amp; Data Law and Ethics: Chiara Gallese, Ph.D.<br><br>[documento]

Siamo usciti con una newsletter in cui l'emergenza, il modo in cui si comunica e i dati relativi, sono i temi principali:
- i dati aperti della piattaforma IT-alert;
- i dati sulle ondate di calore (ma non ci sono i dati grezzi);
- le statistiche sulla popolazione per griglia regolare di Istat;
- comunicare l’emergenza: rimuovere le barriere e dare contesto (il recente caso di Palermo e l'azione delle comunità)

E scorretela tutta: in fondo in "Strumenti/Risorse", ci possono essere delle piccole perle.

